HEADWORD: Odontopteryx
<hw>O`don*top"te*ryx</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>'odoy`s</grk>, <grk>'odo`ntos</grk>, a tooth +
<grk>pte`ryx</grk> a wing.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An extinct
Eocene bird having the jaws strongly serrated, or dentated, but
destitute of true teeth. It was found near London.</def>⟦br⟧
